                            <p>People in need already pay high prices for water, in both time and money. The truth is
                                that many of these families can get a water or sanitation solution in their home for a
                                fraction of their annual water costs. All they need is access to affordable financing to
                                make this a reality. We believed that if given a choice and an opportunity to pay for
                                water and sanitation improvements over a reasonable period of time, millions of people
                                living in poverty would finance long-term solutions versus struggle day-to-day to find
                                that next liter of water.</p>
                            <p>Many financial institutions in developing countries weren’t offering loans for water and
